  <section>
    <div class="service-content">
      <p>In a competitive market like Las Vegas, pricing your home correctly from day one is critical. Too high, and you risk sitting on the market while other homes sell. Too low, and you leave money on the table. A pre-listing appraisal from Las Vegas Appraisal Co. gives sellers and their agents an independent, data-driven valuation before the home ever hits the market.</p>

      <h2>What Is a Pre-Listing Appraisal?</h2>
      <p>A pre-listing appraisal is a full residential appraisal conducted before a property is listed for sale. Just like a lender's appraisal, it involves a physical inspection of the home and a thorough analysis of comparable sales in the surrounding area. The result is a certified, written report that reflects the property's current market value.</p>

      <h2>Benefits of a Pre-Listing Appraisal</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Confident pricing:</strong> Base your list price on real data, not guesswork or online estimates.</li>
        <li><strong>Faster sales:</strong> Correctly priced homes sell faster, with fewer price reductions.</li>
        <li><strong>Stronger negotiations:</strong> Walk into buyer negotiations with an independent appraisal in hand.</li>
        <li><strong>Fewer surprises:</strong> Identify any value-impacting issues before the buyer's lender orders their own appraisal.</li>
        <li><strong>Appeal to cash buyers:</strong> Private buyers especially value having a certified appraisal upfront.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>For Real Estate Agents</h2>
      <p>A pre-listing appraisal is a powerful tool for agents when advising sellers on pricing strategy. It provides an objective third-party valuation you can present to clients who may have unrealistic price expectations — and it gives buyers' agents confidence in the asking price. We work with real estate professionals throughout the Las Vegas Valley and offer volume pricing for high-producing teams and brokerages.</p>

      <h2>Fast Turnaround</h2>
      <p>We understand that listing timelines move quickly. We offer priority scheduling and typically deliver pre-listing appraisal reports within 2–3 business days of the property inspection.</p>

